The paper deals with the queue number of planar graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The specific type of planar graphs studied is planar 3-trees, which are graphs with maximum degree 3 and no cycles of length less than 4, making it relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of graph theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.SI) to analyze and improve the upper bound on the queue number of planar 3-trees.
